The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Thursday, December 18, 2003 				 Student hit in eyes
 OUR CORRESPONDENT Bankura, Dec 17: A first-year  engineering student here had to be hospitalised with bleeding  eyes after he was allegedly beaten up by seniors.																								Manish Dhar of Mallabhum Engineering College was assaulted on Monday night. 																								Classmates rushed a profusely bleeding Dhar to the Bishnupur Subdivisional Hospital from where he was referred to the Calcutta Medical College and Hospital. But those accompanying Dhar took him to the city and left him near his house in Alipore. Residents of the area saw him helpless on the road and took him home. He is now in hospital.																								Superintendent of police Niraj Singh said today trouble began around 11.30 pm on Monday after an argument between Dhar and some of his mates during dinner. We are yet to know the motive behind the attack, he added																								Seven students of the college were arrested today on the basis of a complaint lodged by the college authorities. They were produced in the subdivisional judicial magistrates court and remanded in judicial custody for 14 days, said Singh. We shall know why they beat up Dhar after interrogation, he added.
